	<h2>Writing HEX-Programs</h2>
                        
	<p>
	The language of HEX-programs is an extension of disjunctive datalog.
	It largely implements the <a href="https://www.mat.unical.it/aspcomp2013/files/ASP-CORE-2.01c.pdf">ASP-Core-2 Standard</a>
	and extends it with external atoms.
	</p>

	<p>
	Syntactically, if the language is restricted to programs without external sources,
	it is also strongly related to DLV-syntax.
	The following list displays the language constructs that correspond to DLV (along with the links to the respective DLV-manual section):
	</p>
                        
	<ul>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#AEN178">Facts (EDB)</a></li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#AEN220">Rules (IDB)</a></li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#AEN445">Integrity constraints</a></li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#BUILTIN-COMPARATIVE">Comparative Predicates</a></li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#BUILTIN-ARITHMETIC">Arithmetic Predicates</a></li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#QUERIES">Queries</a> (with <code>--query-enable</code>)</li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#AEN474">Weak Constraints</a> (with <code>--weak-enable</code>)</li>
	  <li><a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#AGGREGATES">Aggregate Predicates</a> (with <code>--aggregate-enable</code>)</li>
	</ul>
	
	<p>
	  Also the <a href="http://www.dlvsystem.com/html/DLV_User_Manual.html#SAFETY">chapter about safety</a> there as well applies to dlvhex.
	</p>

	<p>
    Please see also the <a href="gettingstarted.html">Getting Started</a> guide.
	</p>

